OL,3,CCriminals with devices used in 40% of
OL,4,Ccar thefts face up to five years in
OL,5,Cprison
OL,7,FUnder the law, the burden of proof
OL,8,Fwill be on the owner to demonstrate
OL,9,Fthey were using the device for a
OL,10,Flegitimate purpose.
OL,12,FAccording to the 2022/23 Crime Survey
OL,13,Ffor England and Wales, an offender
OL,14,Fmanipulated a signal from a remote
OL,15,Flocking device in 40% of thefts of
OL,16,Fvehicles.
OL,18,FThere were 732,000 incidents of
OL,19,Fvehicle-related theft in the year
OL,20,Fending September 2024, the Home Office
OL,21,Fsaid.
